He was elected president in 1984, but was overthrown in a U.S.-backed coup in 1990. He was elected again in 2006 and 2011. He is now the longest-serving president in Nicaragua’s history.

Ortega’s election in 2006 was a major victory for the FSLN. It was the first time since the 1990 coup that the FSLN had won a presidential election. The FSLN had been in opposition for 16 years.
